org.gbif.common.parsers

Class DictionaryBackedParser<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.common.parsers.DictionaryBackedParser<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parsable<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileBasedDictionaryParser, LanguageParser

    public class DictionaryBackedParser<K,V>
extends Object
implements Parsable<K,V>
    A simple parser that will initialise with source data, and will use that as a lookup to replace values. This was written with basis of record lookup and country names in mind. Future improvements to this implementation might call a dictionary web service for example, to achieve the same, but allow the abstraction of the dictionary management to a better project (separation of concerns)

        protected K normalize(K value)
        Normalisation of a value used both by adding to the internal dictionary and parsing values. The default does trim and uppercase the value for Strings, but leaves other types unaltered. Override this method to provide specific normalisations for parsers.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
